Style of text, body, images or sections:
========================================
 = <p></p> as definition for a paragraph
 = <br /> (alt) <br> (neu) Umbruch erzwingen
 = <hr /> (alt) <hr> (neu) Horizontale Linie (horizontal ruler)
 
 ==> as a rule, add style via CSS separately and only use HTML for basic layout
 
Images:
=======
 = Add image: <img src="https://www.your-image-source.com/your-image.jpg" alt="Author standing on a beach with two thumbs up. ">
              "alt" ist sehr wichtig als Unterstützung für Vorlese-Programme. Es beschreibt das Bild.
   ODER: Bild im selben Ordner wie das html speicher und dann <img src="html-seminar.jpg">
   ODER mit Unterordner <img src="bilder/html-seminar.jpg">
 = Style image like text in classes (via CSS): <style>.larger-image {width: 500px; height: 30px;}</style>
 = Style right there: <img src="bilder/html-seminar.jpg" width="474" height="66" alt="jetzt HTML lernen">
 = round image: <style>.round-image {border-radius: 50%}</style>
              
  
Anchor elements like to sources outside the page:
=================================================
  = <p>Here's a <a href="http://freecodecamp.com"> link to Free Code Camp</a> for you to follow.</p>
  = Tote Links mit # ersetzen
  = Bilder als Links einsetzen: <a href="#"><img src="https://bit.ly/fcc-running-cats" alt="Three kittens. "></a>
  
  
Listen und Knöpfe:
==================
  = Bullet-Listen (unordred lists): <ul><li>Punkt 1</li><li>Punkt 2</li></ul>
  = Nummerierte Listen (ordred l.): <ol><li>Nummer1</li><li>Nummer2</li></ol>
  = Definitionslisten (definition l.): <dl><dt>Definition Term</dt><dd>Definition Description</dd></dl>
  = Radio-Buttons: <label><input type="radio" name="indoor-outdoor" checked> entweder (schon ausgewählt) </label>
                   <label><input type="radio" name="indoor-outdoor"> oder </label>
  = Check-Boxes:   <label><input type="checkbox" name="personality" checked> Auswahl 1 (schon ausgewählt) </label>
                   <label><input type="checkbox" name="personality"> Auswahl 2 </label>
                   
Ausfüllbares Textfeld:
======================
  = Textfeld erstellen <input type="text"> Plus Placeholder: <input type="text" placeholder="cat photo URL">
  = Inhalt einreichen <form action="/url-where-you-want-to-submit-form-data"></form>
  = Submit-Button <button type="submit">Text on Button</button>
  = required field: <input type="text" required>
              
Felder:
=======
  = <Form></Form> --> alle Textfelder, Checkboxes usw. in diesem Feld werden über denselben Submit-Button gesteuert
  = <div></div>   --> erstellt ein Feld, dessen Format gesammelt gesteuert werden kann.
    
Font awesome:
=============
  = In den header: <link rel="stylesheet" href="//maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/4.5.0/css/font-awesome.min.css"/>
  = add icon to a button: <button class="btn btn-block btn-primary"><i class="fa fa-thumbs-up">Like</i></button>
  = Icons: fa fa-info-circle, fa fa-thumbs-up, fa fa-trash, fa fa-paper-plane (more: http://fontawesome.io/icons/)
  
jQuery:
=======
  = Add the following to the top of your code:
      <script> $(document).ready(function() {
      }); </script>
  = The added commands belong into the {}
  = You target stuff with a "bling" ($)
  = There are three ways of targeting elements: by type: $("button"), by class: $(".btn"), and by id $("#target1").
  = Example:
    $("button").addClass("animated bounce");       targets a type and makes it bounce
    $(".well").addClass("animated shake");         targets a class and makes it shake
    $("#target3").addClass("animated fadeOut");    targets an id and makes it fade out
    $("button").removeClass("btn-default");        removes a class from an object
    $("#target1").css("color", "red");             targets the css of an object and makes it red
    $("#target1").prop("disabled", true)           sets the props of the button to disabled
    $("h3").html("<em>jQuery Playground</em>");    emphasizes the h3 element
    $("h3").text("jQuery Playground");             Alters Text without adding tags
    $("#target4").remove()                         Removes an element
    $("#target4").appendTo("#right-well")          Moves object to another well
    $("#target4").clone().appendTo("#right-well")  Copies object to another well
    $("#target1").parent()                         Targets the parent (the element higher in hierarchy)
    $("#right-well").children()                    Targets the children (elements which inherit props from them)
    $(".target:nth-child(3)").addClass(xy)         Targets the nth child (here the 3th child)
    $(".target:odd").addClass("animated shake");   Targets odd targets (jQuery starts to count at 0, so 2.,4.,6., are odd)
    $(".target:even").addClass("animated shake");  Same
    $("body").addClass("animated hinge");          Targets whole body (=everything) and makes it hinge on the topleft corner ^^
    
